Should be easy to take care of.

01:15.909 --> 01:17.643
It's great.

01:17.677 --> 01:19.745
Um, I have to go.

01:19.779 --> 01:22.681
Of course.
Um...

01:22.716 --> 01:24.283
Now that I'm living here,

01:24.317 --> 01:26.552
I hope we can spend
some time together.

01:26.586 --> 01:28.320
Get to know each other again.

01:28.355 --> 01:31.290
Yeah.

01:31.324 --> 01:33.258
I really do have to go.

01:37.897 --> 01:39.832
- <i>( Rock music playing )</i>
<i>- ♪ Oh oh oh</i>

01:41.868 --> 01:44.169
this is the ultimate irony
that dad is sponsoring

01:44.204 --> 01:46.972
- a motorcycle show.
- I don't think that he hates motorcycles.

01:47.007 --> 01:48.173
I think he just
hates us on them.

01:48.208 --> 01:50.776
Well, it's good
for business, so...

01:50.810 --> 01:52.077
Well, I for one
cannot wait to see

01:52.112 --> 01:54.613
50 hogs and the biker
chicks who love them

01:54.648 --> 01:55.981
- all around dad.
- ( Both laughing )

01:56.016 --> 01:58.684
- He's gonna be so freaked out.
- John: <i>Son of a bitch!</i>

02:01.855 --> 02:03.522
- Yikes.
- Damn.

02:03.556 --> 02:05.424
Can you believe it?

02:05.458 --> 02:06.725
They came back.

02:06.760 --> 02:09.360
- Who's they?
- The people that did this before.

02:09.395 --> 02:12.231
How do you know
it's the same people?

02:12.265 --> 02:15.034
Obviously, they were mad that
we painted over the first one.

02:15.068 --> 02:17.036
But you must see
the difference between

02:17.070 --> 02:18.971
the girl that was
painted here yesterday and

02:19.005 --> 02:20.172
<i>this.</i>

02:20.206 --> 02:22.107
Uh... no.

02:22.142 --> 02:24.777
You're honestly telling me

02:24.811 --> 02:26.045
that you don't see
the difference between

02:26.079 --> 02:27.212
a figurative drawing and a tag?

02:27.247 --> 02:29.014
- It's all just...
- It's all just graffiti.

02:29.049 --> 02:30.949
Which is not a bad word, dad!

02:30.984 --> 02:33.886
If it's done without
my consent, it's a crime.

02:33.920 --> 02:36.088
I refuse to believe that you can't
see the difference between the two.

02:36.122 --> 02:37.990
It's all the same continuum.
Yeah, I'll give you that.

02:38.024 --> 02:39.825
- It's all art...
- Art?! Are you serious?

02:39.859 --> 02:40.893
You're calling this art?

02:40.927 --> 02:42.661
Obviously not in
the traditional sense

02:42.696 --> 02:43.829
- of the word.
- In what sense of the word

02:43.863 --> 02:45.030
would it be art?
Come on!

02:45.065 --> 02:46.799
This is no better than
breaking and entering.

02:46.833 --> 02:48.033
It's the same as
breaking and entering,

02:48.068 --> 02:49.668
really? It's the
same thing?

02:49.703 --> 02:51.904
It is gangbangers
destroying private property.

02:51.938 --> 02:53.639
Let me explain
something to you, okay?

02:53.673 --> 02:55.774
I worked very hard
to own this wall.

02:55.809 --> 02:59.411
If want someone to paint it,
I will ask them to do so.

02:59.446 --> 03:02.548
Dad, it is people who
are otherwise invisible

03:02.582 --> 03:05.384
expressing themselves, communicating
in the only way they know how.

03:05.418 --> 03:07.186
They're taking a spray can.
They're saying,

03:07.220 --> 03:08.420
"here I am!
This is me!

03:08.455 --> 03:10.122
- See me."
- Are you kidding me?!

03:10.156 --> 03:12.191
That is the stupidest thing I have
ever heard in my entire life.

03:12.225 --> 03:15.094
I will paint over this
again and again and again.

03:15.128 --> 03:18.263
Day in, day out. I
will not let them win.

